feat: CLI subcommand framework with manual dispatch (he-9eq)

Refactor cmd/herald/main.go from simple if/else dispatch to proper
subcommand handling with backward compatibility.

Subcommands:
- serve: start the daemon (default when no command given)
- dash: launch terminal dashboard
- migrate up|down|status: database migration management
- auth google: interactive OAuth2 flow with localhost callback
  and macOS Keychain token storage
- version: build info (version, commit, date, go version)
- help: usage information

Extracted loadConfig() and makeLogger() helpers for reuse across
subcommands. Migrate up applies sql/*.sql files in order. Auth
google uses ephemeral localhost HTTP server for OAuth2 callback.
